  <original-body>Currently, the following doesn't raise any error:

@@@
t = Time.now.in_time_zone(&quot;There is no such timezone&quot;); t.utc
@@@

Many other methods of `TimeWithZone` will raise a `NoMethodError` as soon as they try to access the timezone (e.g. `t.inspect`).

It should not be possible to create a TimeWithZone with an invalid timezone.</original-body>
